  <div class="not-prose bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm text-[#555] leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge supplies two types of industrial wastewater centrifuges: disc stack centrifuges (up to 12,000 Gs, sub-micron separation for low-sludge wastewater under 10% solids) and decanter centrifuges (2,000–4,000 Gs, continuous cake discharge for high-sludge wastewater over 10% solids). Applications include semiconductor wastewater, oily wastewater, battery manufacturing wastewater, municipal biosolids, mining tailings, and food processing waste. Based in Warren, Michigan, Dolphin Centrifuge has over 40 years of wastewater centrifuge experience.</p>
